<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="2913" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[160,1156,1113,1728]" pageId="4" pageNumber="2913">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,271,1113,1139]" pageId="4" pageNumber="2913">Remarks.</emphasis>
The genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Milne-Edwards" authorityYear="1840" box="[412,506,1114,1139]" class="Malacostraca" family="Aegidae" genus="Alitropus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="4" pageNumber="2913" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[412,506,1114,1139]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="2913">Alitropus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is so far considered to be monospecific and it was established by 
<bibRefCitation author="Milne Edwards" box="[264,493,1149,1174]" firstAuthor="Milne Edwards" pageId="4" pageNumber="2913" refId="ref10174" refString="Milne Edwards H. 1840. Histoire Naturelle des Crustaces Comprenent l'anatomie, la physiologie et la classification de ces animaux. Paris: Roret; p. 638." type="journal volume" year="1840">Milne Edwards (1840</bibRefCitation>
, p. 245) for the species 
<taxonomicName authorityName="H. Milne Edwards" authorityYear="1840" box="[749,906,1149,1174]" class="Malacostraca" family="Aegidae" genus="Alitropus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="4" pageNumber="2913" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="typus">
<emphasis box="[749,906,1149,1174]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="2913">
Alitropus 
<typeStatus box="[849,906,1149,1174]" pageId="4" pageNumber="2913">typus</typeStatus>
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
collected in the Bay of Bengal. Later, 
<bibRefCitation author="Schioedte and Meinert" box="[321,649,1183,1208]" firstAuthor="Schioedte" pageId="4" pageNumber="2913" pagination="321 - 414" refId="ref10651" refString="Schioedte JC, Meinert F. 1879. Symbolae ad monographium Cymothoarum crustaceorum isopodum familiae. Naturh Tidskr Ser. 3 (12): 321 - 414." type="journal article" year="1879">Schioedte and Meinert (1879</bibRefCitation>
, p. 402) described another species, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schioedte and Meinert" authorityYear="1879" class="Malacostraca" family="Aegidae" genus="Alitropus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="4" pageNumber="2913" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="foveolatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="2913">Alitropus foveolatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, from an unknown locality, but this addition was assumed to be based on the male 
<taxonomicName authorityName="H. Milne Edwards" authorityYear="1840" box="[221,305,1253,1278]" class="Malacostraca" family="Aegidae" genus="Alitropus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="4" pageNumber="2913" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="typus">
<emphasis box="[221,305,1253,1278]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="2913">
A. 
<typeStatus box="[248,305,1253,1278]" pageId="4" pageNumber="2913">typus</typeStatus>
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
– this species exhibiting considerable sexual dimorphism in the shape of the body. 
<bibRefCitation author="Pillai" box="[232,362,1287,1312]" firstAuthor="Pillai" pageId="4" pageNumber="2913" pagination="1 - 22" refId="ref10395" refString="Pillai NK. 1954. A preliminary note on the Tanaidacea and Isopoda of Travancore. Bull Cent Res Inst Univ Travancore Trivandrum. 3: 1 - 22." type="journal article" year="1954">Pillai (1954)</bibRefCitation>
gave a preliminary description of a new species, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pillai" authorityYear="1954" box="[931,1149,1287,1312]" class="Malacostraca" family="Aegidae" genus="Alitropus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="4" pageNumber="2913" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dimorphus">
<emphasis box="[931,1149,1287,1312]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="2913">Alitropus dimorphus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, from Travancore waters, but in a letter to the 
<collectingCountry box="[657,748,1322,1347]" name="India" pageId="4" pageNumber="2913">Bombay</collectingCountry>
Natural History Society (BNHS) dated 
<date box="[160,374,1357,1382]" pageId="4" pageNumber="2913" value="1955-11-21">21 November 1955</date>
, he said that he had re-examined his material and had concluded that these specimens were a variant of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="H. Milne Edwards" authorityYear="1840" box="[547,632,1391,1416]" class="Malacostraca" family="Aegidae" genus="Alitropus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="4" pageNumber="2913" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="typus">
<emphasis box="[547,632,1391,1416]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="2913">
A. 
<typeStatus box="[575,632,1391,1416]" pageId="4" pageNumber="2913">typus</typeStatus>
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[160,1156,1113,1728]" pageId="4" pageNumber="2913">
Later, 
<bibRefCitation author="Weber" box="[269,429,1426,1451]" firstAuthor="Weber" pageId="4" pageNumber="2913" pagination="528 - 571" refId="ref11032" refString="Weber M. 1892. Die Susswasser-Crustaceen des Indischen Archipels.. .. Zoologische Ergebnisse einer Reise in Niederlandisch Ost-Indien. 2: 528 - 571." type="journal article" year="1892">Weber (1892)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Nierstrasz and De Marees van Swinderen" box="[497,1080,1426,1451]" firstAuthor="Nierstrasz" pageId="4" pageNumber="2913" pagination="394 - 402" refId="ref10277" refString="Nierstrasz HF, De Marees van Swinderen JW. 1931. Susswasser-Isopoden der Limnolo gischen Sunda-Expedition. Archiv Fur Hydrobiolgie. 9: 394 - 402." type="journal article" year="1931">Nierstrasz and De Marees van Swinderen (1931)</bibRefCitation>
questioned the validity of this genus and regarded it as synonymous with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1818" box="[1054,1149,1461,1486]" class="Malacostraca" family="Aegidae" genus="Rocinela" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="4" pageNumber="2913" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1054,1149,1461,1486]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="2913">Rocinela</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Stebbing" box="[160,358,1495,1520]" firstAuthor="Stebbing" pageId="4" pageNumber="2913" pagination="179 - 191" refId="ref10856" refString="Stebbing TRR. 1911. Indian isopods. Rec Indian Mus. 6: 179 - 191. doi: 10.5962 / bhl. part. 21332." type="journal article" year="1911">Stebbing (1911)</bibRefCitation>
, however, thought that the genus was valid. 
<bibRefCitation author="Stebbing" box="[959,1156,1495,1520]" firstAuthor="Stebbing" pageId="4" pageNumber="2913" pagination="179 - 191" refId="ref10856" refString="Stebbing TRR. 1911. Indian isopods. Rec Indian Mus. 6: 179 - 191. doi: 10.5962 / bhl. part. 21332." type="journal article" year="1911">Stebbing (1911)</bibRefCitation>
pointed out that the pereopods were slender and unarmed, whereas in species of the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1818" box="[298,393,1565,1590]" class="Malacostraca" family="Aegidae" genus="Rocinela" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="4" pageNumber="2913" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[298,393,1565,1590]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="2913">Rocinela</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the corresponding pereopods are stout and are armed with robust setae. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Milne-Edwards" authorityYear="1840" box="[327,427,1599,1624]" class="Malacostraca" family="Aegidae" genus="Alitropus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="4" pageNumber="2913" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[327,427,1599,1624]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="2913">Alitropus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1818" box="[590,685,1599,1624]" class="Malacostraca" family="Aegidae" genus="Rocinela" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="4" pageNumber="2913" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[590,685,1599,1624]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="2913">Rocinela</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in lacking afrontal cephalic projection and in having slender pereopods that lack an enlarged propodus. 
<bibRefCitation author="Bruce" box="[950,1097,1634,1659]" firstAuthor="Bruce" pageId="4" pageNumber="2913" pagination="757 - 788" refId="ref9714" refString="Bruce NL. 1983. Aegidae (Isopoda: Crustacea) from Australia with descriptions of three new species. J Nat Hist. 17 (5): 757 - 788. doi: 10.1080 / 00222938300770591." type="journal article" year="1983">Bruce (1983)</bibRefCitation>
is of the view that the highly reduced coxae on pereonites 5–7 separate 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Milne-Edwards" authorityYear="1840" box="[989,1089,1669,1694]" class="Malacostraca" family="Aegidae" genus="Alitropus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="4" pageNumber="2913" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[989,1089,1669,1694]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="2913">Alitropus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the other aegid genera.
</paragraph>
